        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>January 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philada</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">I last had this pleasure<lb/> under date of <date>16<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> ultimo. Enclosing <persName>E. H. Clark Dodge</persName> <date>16th</date><lb/> <add>&#63;</add> on <persName>E. H. Clark &#38; Co</persName> <placeName>Philad</placeName> for one Hundred Dollars<lb/> for which I am without any acknowledgment. Well<lb/> you have the goodness to say whither you received it<lb/> or not.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I now hand you enclosed <persName>Wm. A. Sale</persName> for check for<lb/> one Hundred Dollars. Enclosed to give order and<lb/> marked <hi rend="underline">good</hi> by the Teller. This will be taken by<lb/> your Banks on deposit&#44; and I presume will answer<lb/> your purpose quite as well as a <add>&#63;</add> on a <placeName>Philada</placeName><lb/> House</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The check referred to above is dated this day No 1345<lb/> on the Bank of North America</p>
			<p>Hope soon to make you additional remittances</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">In great haste</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">W S. Canford</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
